	        		        	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Programdesign:Design Cheat Sheet</h1>
				<div id="bodyContent">
		            <h3 id="siteSub">From Coursera</h3>
		            <div id="contentSub"></div>
		            		            		            					<!-- start content -->
					<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p>The Design Cheat Sheet lays out each step you take when using the How to Design Programs recipe. If you have only learned <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://class.coursera.org/programdesign-002/wiki/view?page=HtDFunctions">HtDF</a> or <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://class.coursera.org/programdesign-002/wiki/view?page=HtDData">HtDD</a> you may be better off visiting their respective pages. </p>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="HtDW">HtDW</span></h2>
<ol>
<li>Domain analysis (use a piece of paper!)

<ol>
<li>Sketch program scenarios</li>
<li>Identify constant information</li>
<li>Identify changing information</li>
<li>Identify big-bang options</li>
</ol></li>
<li>Build the actual program

<ol>
<li>Constants (based on 1.2 above)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/index.php/Data_definition" title="Data definition">Data definition</a> (based on 1.3 above)</li>
<li>Functions
<ul><li>. main first (based on 1.3, 1.4 and 2.2 above)
</li><li>. wish list entries for <a href="/wiki/index.php?title=Big-bang&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Big-bang (page does not exist)">big-bang</a> handlers</li>
</li></ul>
<li>Work through wish list until done</li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="HtDD">HtDD</span></h2>
<ol>
<li>A possible <a href="/wiki/index.php?title=Structure_definition&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Structure definition (page does not exist)">structure definition</a>.</li>
<li>A <a href="/wiki/index.php?title=Type_comment&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Type comment (page does not exist)">type comment</a> that defines a new type name and describes how to form data of that type.</li>
<li>An interpretation that describes the correspondence between information and data.</li>
<li>One or more examples of the data.</li>
<li>A <a href="/wiki/index.php/Template" title="Template">template</a> for a 1 argument function operating on data of this type.</li>
</ol>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="HtDF">HtDF</span></h2>
<ol>
<li><a href="/wiki/index.php/Signature" title="Signature">Signature</a>, <a href="/wiki/index.php/Purpose" title="Purpose">purpose</a> and <a href="/wiki/index.php/Stub" title="Stub">stub</a>.</li>
<li>Define examples, wrap each in check-expect.</li>
<li>Template and inventory.</li>
<li>Code the function body.</li>
<li>Test and debug until correct</li>
</ol>

